WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:16.360
Monster House Chapter 1 Do you want to die?

00:16.360 --> 00:25.160
It was the afternoon before Halloween. A little girl was on her bike in Oak Street in Mayville.

00:25.160 --> 00:31.520
She went happily between the trees and the lovely gardens. But then her bike went on

00:31.520 --> 00:40.120
to a front lawn and she stopped. There was a strange sound and she looked up. The lawn

00:40.120 --> 00:47.760
was in front of a big old house. There were two windows over the front door. The windows

00:47.760 --> 00:54.280
looked down at her angrily. There was a loud shout and an old man came out of the house.

00:54.280 --> 01:05.200
It was Mr. Nebbercracker. Get off my lawn. He shouted, Do you want to die? The little

01:05.200 --> 01:12.040
girl was frightened and she ran away. Mr. Nebbercracker walked across the lawn and took

01:12.040 --> 01:22.920
the bike. And don't come back. These children, he said, they never listen. The sound came again.

01:22.920 --> 01:31.200
It was louder and then it stopped. Mr. Nebbercracker went into his house and closed the door.

01:31.200 --> 01:41.200
DJ Walters lived opposite Mr. Nebbercracker's house. DJ saw everything and wrote about it in

01:41.200 --> 01:50.720
his book. There was a lot of writing in the book. Today he wrote, 30th October, end took

01:50.720 --> 02:01.120
bike. DJ, his mum called, I'm coming. DJ looked at the pictures on the walls of his bedroom.

02:01.120 --> 02:10.720
They were photos of Mr. Nebbercracker's house. DJ, she called again. DJ ran out of his house.

02:10.720 --> 02:22.440
His mum and dad were in the car. Mom said DJ, he took a bike again. DJ, she said, you can't stay

02:22.440 --> 02:28.480
in your room for hours to watch an old man. But there's something wrong with that house.

02:28.480 --> 02:38.160
We're going, said his dad. Zee is coming soon. She's staying with you tonight. We love you,

02:38.240 --> 02:47.360
called his mum and they drove away. Then a boy with a ball came across the street. It was

02:47.360 --> 02:56.880
chowder. DJ's best friend. It's Halloween soon, said chowder. What are you going to wear?

02:56.880 --> 03:06.920
I'm not going trick or treating this year, said DJ. But we always do. We're too old now.

03:06.920 --> 03:14.680
Chowder tried to throw his ball into the basket on the wall. He turned and looked at DJ.

03:14.680 --> 03:21.400
Be careful, shouted DJ. Chowder turned back and the ball hit him.

03:21.400 --> 03:34.760
Chowder put his hand on his nose. Are you okay? Ask DJ. Then he saw the ball. Oh no. It was on

03:34.760 --> 03:42.040
Mr. Nebbercracker's nice lawn. Your older DJ, you get it, said chowder.

03:42.760 --> 03:52.840
No, said DJ. But it was expensive. Maybe Mr. Nebbercracker is sleeping. DJ looked at the house.

03:53.960 --> 04:01.080
Okay. He put one foot on the lawn. The ball was close. He ran to it.

04:01.800 --> 04:10.680
Suddenly the door opened and Mr. Nebbercracker came out. Who? DJ moved quickly. His shoe pulled

04:10.680 --> 04:18.920
out a bit of the lawn. I'm sorry, cried DJ. He wanted to run but Mr. Nebbercracker held his shirt.

04:18.920 --> 04:29.880
Do you want to die? shouted Mr. Nebbercracker. No, I love life. Mr. Nebbercracker pulled DJ's shirt.

04:30.600 --> 04:34.840
This is my house. He shouted. Stay away.

04:36.440 --> 04:45.240
The old man's face was very red and his eyes went big. Suddenly he fell on top of DJ on the lawn.

04:46.280 --> 04:56.600
The old man didn't move. Oh, said chowder. Then there was a cold wind and the door closed loudly.

05:00.840 --> 05:08.840
Chapter 2. Come in.

05:11.480 --> 05:14.520
Some people came and took Mr. Nebbercracker away.

05:15.800 --> 05:21.800
He's dead because of me. DJ said to chowder. I feel terrible.

05:21.880 --> 05:28.760
Oh, just then Zee arrived in her car. She took her bag into DJ's house.

05:29.720 --> 05:34.520
Hi, she smiled. We're going to have a very good time.

05:35.960 --> 05:42.200
Mom and Dad aren't here, said DJ. Zee stopped smiling.

05:43.160 --> 05:50.440
Okay, she said, in the house at 9 o'clock, in your room at 11. No games.

05:51.400 --> 05:59.800
Are not a child. Zee just looked at him angrily. Later, DJ was in his room.

06:00.840 --> 06:07.480
He looked at the house across the street. The house looked at him. He saw some smoke.

06:08.440 --> 06:15.240
It came out of the top of the house. Then there was a cold wind again and he closed his window.

06:16.760 --> 06:24.280
DJ went to sleep. He had a bad dream about the house. The house came into his room.

06:25.080 --> 06:34.520
It was big and dark. Then the dark was a hand. It wanted to suddenly the phone woke him up.

06:35.480 --> 06:38.600
DJ looked at the number. He was frightened.

06:39.720 --> 06:47.080
The call was from Mr. Nevercracker's house. Who was it? Then someone was in his room.

06:47.880 --> 06:56.680
Boo! It was Bones, Zee's boyfriend. Bones laughed at DJ. Zee was there too.

06:57.400 --> 07:04.440
It isn't funny, shouted DJ. Mr. Nevercracker's dead and someone is in his house.

07:05.480 --> 07:12.520
Boo! said Zee in Bones. They didn't believe him. They laughed and left his room.

07:13.880 --> 07:18.440
DJ looked at the house. One of the windows opened like an eye.

07:19.400 --> 07:26.120
DJ's heart went faster. The window closed again. DJ used his phone.

07:27.560 --> 07:29.800
Police answered Chowder.

07:30.600 --> 07:33.800
The danger zone said DJ. Now!

07:36.040 --> 07:43.800
Bones told Zee the story of his beautiful red kite. He was ten and he loved that kite more than

07:43.800 --> 07:49.560
anything. Bones looked happy. But then his face changed.

07:50.840 --> 07:57.080
One day the kite was high in the sky. But then it came down behind the houses.

07:58.040 --> 08:04.920
He found it on Mr. Nevercracker's lawn. The old man shouted at him and took the kite.

08:05.640 --> 08:08.920
He's a terrible old man, said Zee.

08:09.640 --> 08:14.760
Yeah, said Bones. And he's strange. He talked to the house.

08:15.560 --> 08:19.800
People say his wife died in that house. Did he eat her?

08:20.680 --> 08:26.520
He laughed. But Zee was angry. She said, go home Bones.

08:28.280 --> 08:33.240
Bones went out of DJ's house. He looked at Mr. Nevercracker's house.

08:34.200 --> 08:38.040
He threw a trainer onto the lawn. Nothing happened.

08:39.160 --> 08:46.920
Then he walked on the lawn. He waited. Nothing. He danced on the lawn.

08:47.640 --> 08:55.800
You are dead, he shouted. Look at me. I'm on your lawn. What are you going to do?

08:56.040 --> 09:05.400
Suddenly the door opened and Bones saw his lovely red kite. Bones followed it.

09:06.520 --> 09:12.840
The door closed and there was a terrible sound. Then it was quiet again.

09:15.080 --> 09:22.520
The danger zone was DJ and Chowder's special place. There was a very big crane and a digger

09:22.600 --> 09:23.640
and a lot of holes.

09:24.760 --> 09:32.280
Mr. Nevercracker is back from the dead, said DJ. He wants to find me. I need your help, Chowder.

09:33.560 --> 09:39.080
The two boys left the danger zone and soon they were in front of Mr. Nevercracker's house.

09:40.120 --> 09:47.080
They saw a trainer on the lawn. The house watched them. Two windows opened slowly.

09:47.880 --> 09:48.680
Then nothing.

09:49.640 --> 09:54.200
Doosh's boring, said Chowder, and he went onto the lawn.

09:54.920 --> 10:04.200
Don't, shouted DJ. Suddenly there was a terrible sound. The door opened and the windows moved.

10:05.160 --> 10:06.760
They looked down angrily.

10:08.840 --> 10:15.640
Then the floor opened like teeth in a mouth. There was a big red open throat

10:16.600 --> 10:21.720
and then the carpet came out of the door like a tongue. The boys ran.

10:31.400 --> 10:34.520
Chapter 3 We don't believe you.

10:36.760 --> 10:42.120
The next morning a young girl came to the door. It was Jenny Bennett.

10:42.920 --> 10:48.520
You need some treats for tonight, she said. I'm selling chocolates.

10:49.800 --> 10:52.360
It's not my house, said Z.

10:53.480 --> 11:00.360
Okay, said Jenny. I'm sure the mom and dad left you some money for the trick or treaters.

11:01.320 --> 11:07.960
You give me $20 for some chocolates. I say you gave me $30.

11:08.760 --> 11:13.400
You keep $10 and you can have the chocolates too.

11:14.440 --> 11:18.680
Hey, you're good. Z gave Jenny the money.

11:21.240 --> 11:22.920
Z went to DJ's room.

11:24.120 --> 11:26.280
What are you doing? She asked.

11:27.560 --> 11:34.200
Something in that house tried to eat us, said DJ. We stayed up all night to watch.

11:35.080 --> 11:38.520
You're so strange, said Z.

11:39.560 --> 11:44.200
Do you know where Bones is? He left last night and didn't come back.

11:45.320 --> 11:48.280
Didn't come back, said Jouda.

11:49.560 --> 11:55.560
Zee, I'm sorry, but the house took your boyfriend, said DJ.

11:57.080 --> 12:00.120
Zee didn't believe them. She closed her eyes.

12:01.080 --> 12:05.720
Please. She threw some chocolates to DJ.

12:06.920 --> 12:10.040
Breakfast, she said, and left the room.

12:11.640 --> 12:13.640
Zee looked out of the window again.

12:14.920 --> 12:25.160
Oh, he said. DJ looked. It was Jenny. The boys watched her. They liked her red hair.

12:26.040 --> 12:30.120
They also liked her little nose and big clever eyes.

12:31.560 --> 12:35.240
Zee looked at DJ. I saw her first.

12:36.040 --> 12:40.760
You can't say that, said DJ. Oh, yes, I can.

12:43.240 --> 12:47.240
Jenny started to go to Mr. Nebbercracker's door with her chocolates.

12:48.120 --> 12:53.960
The boys ran out. No, they shouted. Jenny looked at them.

12:55.160 --> 12:57.800
Do you have a problem? She asked.

12:59.400 --> 13:03.880
Suddenly the windows opened. They were red and angry.

13:05.320 --> 13:10.440
Then a terrible cry came from the house and the lawn moved up and down.

13:11.960 --> 13:15.640
The door opened and the kids saw the mouth and the teeth.

13:16.760 --> 13:20.920
The carpet tongue came out and lifted Jenny up and down.

13:21.800 --> 13:25.640
It took the chocolates, but the boys pulled Jenny back.

13:27.080 --> 13:34.520
Hey! It was Zee. The lawn and the house went quiet. The door closed.

13:35.480 --> 13:41.880
The eyes were windows again. I'm going to find bones and she went off.

13:43.240 --> 13:45.560
What's happening? Asked Jenny.

13:46.360 --> 13:49.080
The boys told Jenny about the house.

13:49.960 --> 13:52.520
I'm very busy, said Jenny.

13:53.160 --> 13:59.720
But that house took my chocolates and tried to eat me. I can give you one hour.

14:01.240 --> 14:04.760
They all looked at the house. It was quiet now.

14:06.040 --> 14:09.800
Then they saw a dog. It walked onto the lawn.

14:10.760 --> 14:15.000
The door opened and the tongue came out. It took the dog.

14:15.720 --> 14:16.840
It was very quick.

14:18.120 --> 14:23.160
Call the police, said Jenny. Suddenly DJ remembered.

14:23.960 --> 14:29.960
It's Halloween. Tonight there are going to be a lot of children at that door trick or treating.

14:30.600 --> 14:31.880
They're all going to die.

14:33.400 --> 14:37.320
Then the door opened and there was Chowder's ball.

14:38.600 --> 14:44.120
Suddenly the ball changed. Now it was a Halloween monster face.

14:44.760 --> 14:47.960
It's laughing at us, said Jenny.

14:49.240 --> 14:51.000
Then the police arrived.

14:53.000 --> 14:58.280
There were two policemen. Lander's was fat and had a pink face.

14:59.400 --> 15:03.480
Okay. What's happening? Lander's asked.

15:04.520 --> 15:08.920
The other policeman, Lister, was tall. He shouted at them.

15:09.640 --> 15:12.200
All of you, next to the car, now.

15:13.080 --> 15:16.280
Oh, he's new, said Lander's.

15:17.480 --> 15:21.400
There's something very bad in that house, Jenny told them.

15:22.120 --> 15:27.800
Someone died, said DJ. A dog died too, said Chowder.

15:29.480 --> 15:33.800
Lander's smiled, but Lister shouted into the police radio.

15:34.440 --> 15:38.200
Dead dog, dead dog. We have a problem here.

15:39.080 --> 15:41.960
Lander's took the radio away from him.

15:42.840 --> 15:48.440
Okay, you three. It's Halloween. We are busy.

15:49.560 --> 15:55.320
DJ tried again. Please believe us. The house has a mouth.

15:55.960 --> 15:58.360
It pulls things in and eats them.

15:59.640 --> 16:02.040
See you later, said Lander's.

16:03.160 --> 16:06.520
Look. DJ walked onto the lawn.

16:07.480 --> 16:11.480
Nothing. He danced on the lawn. Nothing.

16:12.760 --> 16:18.920
Okay, said Lander's. We are going. Leave this house now.

16:19.800 --> 16:26.120
I'm going to give you ten. A one, two, three.

16:26.760 --> 16:33.480
But we need your help, cried Jenny. Four, five, six.

16:34.280 --> 16:39.240
The three kids looked at the policeman. They weren't going to help.

16:40.520 --> 16:43.080
DJ Chowder and Jenny walked away.

16:44.360 --> 16:47.480
What can we do now, asked Chowder?

16:48.440 --> 16:54.600
I have an idea, said DJ. Let's ask a very clever person.

17:04.120 --> 17:07.240
Chapter four, Thomas McTabbelis.

17:08.760 --> 17:13.560
The pizza freak was a cheap restaurant with a lot of computer games.

17:14.600 --> 17:20.680
A big man was playing one. His shirt and pizza freak hat were dirty.

17:21.960 --> 17:26.840
This is skull, said DJ importantly. He knows everything.

17:27.640 --> 17:32.280
Let's talk to him, said Jenny, and she walked over to Skull.

17:33.320 --> 17:39.240
He turned. His face was very white and his eyes were red and tired.

17:40.200 --> 17:41.880
What? I'm busy.

17:43.320 --> 17:48.680
DJ was quick. There's a monster in Mr. Nebbercracker's house.

17:49.240 --> 17:51.400
It must die before it eats us.

17:52.760 --> 17:53.640
Okay, ma'am.

17:54.680 --> 17:55.960
Skull played his game.

17:56.600 --> 17:58.680
His hands moved very quickly.

17:59.560 --> 18:03.000
Sometimes a person loves his house very much.

18:03.720 --> 18:04.680
Then he dies.

18:05.880 --> 18:08.760
That dead person can live in the house.

18:09.560 --> 18:12.200
It's in the walls and the floor.

18:12.840 --> 18:15.960
It's called Thomas McTabbelis.

18:17.000 --> 18:19.880
That means monster house, said Jenny.

18:20.680 --> 18:22.840
I knew that, said Chowder.

18:23.560 --> 18:24.520
Can we stop it?

18:25.160 --> 18:26.040
Ask DJ.

18:26.840 --> 18:28.840
Find the heart of the house.

18:29.720 --> 18:32.120
The heart must die.

18:33.240 --> 18:35.400
So where's the heart?

18:36.120 --> 18:37.000
Ask Chowder.

18:37.960 --> 18:39.000
No one answered.

18:40.280 --> 18:41.800
Then DJ remembered.

18:43.320 --> 18:45.160
Smoke comes from the house.

18:46.040 --> 18:49.160
The heart of the house must be the fire.

18:50.280 --> 18:51.800
We must stop the fire.

18:53.720 --> 18:56.440
We don't have much time, said Jenny.

18:57.080 --> 18:59.000
We must find a way to get in.

19:00.360 --> 19:02.760
I've got an idea, said DJ.

19:03.800 --> 19:06.120
First, let's make something.

19:06.760 --> 19:08.600
It must be like a person.

19:09.720 --> 19:12.200
We put sleep easy drinking it.

19:13.000 --> 19:17.080
The house eats the person and goes to sleep.

19:17.960 --> 19:21.320
Then we go in and find the fire.

19:22.600 --> 19:26.120
That's a very stupid plan, said Chowder.

19:26.680 --> 19:29.080
I don't want to go into a monster.

19:30.680 --> 19:31.960
Jenny looked at DJ.

19:32.840 --> 19:33.480
It's good.

19:34.200 --> 19:34.920
Let's do it.

19:36.200 --> 19:38.920
Okay, said Chowder quickly.

19:38.920 --> 19:39.640
Let's do it.

19:41.080 --> 19:45.880
DJ found an old carpet cleaner and Jenny put some clothes on it.

19:46.680 --> 19:48.760
It was like a Halloween monster.

19:49.880 --> 19:53.080
They put some sleep easy drink into the cleaner.

19:53.960 --> 19:54.760
They were ready.

19:56.680 --> 19:57.560
It was evening.

19:58.200 --> 20:00.840
The tops of the houses were red in the sun.

20:02.200 --> 20:03.480
Trick or treat!

20:04.520 --> 20:05.960
Chowder called to the house.

20:07.320 --> 20:10.520
The windows opened and looked at the carpet cleaner.

20:11.400 --> 20:12.920
There was hate in the eyes.

20:13.720 --> 20:17.560
Start the cleaner, said DJ quietly.

20:19.000 --> 20:21.080
The carpet cleaner started to move.

20:22.040 --> 20:23.480
It went to the front door.

20:24.680 --> 20:30.200
The door opened and there were the teeth, ready, waiting.

20:31.560 --> 20:34.120
DJ Chowder and Jenny smiled.

20:35.640 --> 20:38.520
Suddenly they heard the sound of a police car.

20:39.560 --> 20:42.440
The house's eyes and mouth closed

20:42.440 --> 20:45.000
and the carpet cleaner stopped in front of the door.

20:46.440 --> 20:48.200
Lander saw the carpet cleaner.

20:49.000 --> 20:49.880
What's this?

20:50.840 --> 20:53.960
He looked at it and found the sleep easy drink.

20:55.240 --> 20:58.440
Okay, you're going to the police station.

20:59.560 --> 21:02.520
Lister shouted, right in the car.

21:03.960 --> 21:06.360
Listen to us, shouted DJ.

21:06.360 --> 21:07.960
The house is a monster.

21:07.960 --> 21:12.360
The policeman put the three kids into the car.

21:13.320 --> 21:17.800
And don't try to open the doors because you can't, said Lister.

21:19.240 --> 21:22.280
Suddenly a terrible sound came from the house.

21:23.320 --> 21:23.880
What's that?

21:25.160 --> 21:26.440
Lister walked to the door.

21:27.400 --> 21:28.520
Lander's followed him.

21:29.640 --> 21:33.560
No, get away from the house, shouted DJ.

21:34.520 --> 21:37.000
He and Jenny tried to open the car doors.

21:37.960 --> 21:39.640
He's right, said Jenny.

21:40.200 --> 21:41.400
We can't get out.

21:50.920 --> 21:54.680
Chapter five, Constance the Giantess.

21:56.920 --> 21:58.520
Lister ran onto the lawn.

21:59.160 --> 21:59.960
It moved.

22:01.000 --> 22:03.560
A tree near him started to move too.

22:04.440 --> 22:07.480
He tried to run, but the tree pulled him back.

22:08.920 --> 22:11.400
Suddenly he was high in the sky.

22:12.360 --> 22:13.000
Help!

22:13.560 --> 22:14.040
He called.

22:15.320 --> 22:21.000
Lander's tried to run to the car, but the carpet tongue came through the door and pulled him in.

22:22.280 --> 22:25.800
Then the tree threw Lister into the house after him.

22:26.920 --> 22:28.520
The kids didn't want to look.

22:29.880 --> 22:33.560
The tree took the car and held it high over the lawn.

22:34.520 --> 22:36.760
The front door mouth was bigger now.

22:37.960 --> 22:40.520
I'm only here because of you, DJ.

22:41.160 --> 22:42.200
Shouted chowder.

22:42.840 --> 22:43.720
No, you're not.

22:44.280 --> 22:47.080
You're here because of her, cried DJ.

22:47.880 --> 22:49.720
The car was closer to the mouth.

22:50.520 --> 22:52.600
Be quiet, said Jenny.

22:53.160 --> 22:55.080
We've got a big problem.

22:57.240 --> 22:59.480
The tree threw the car into the house.

23:00.280 --> 23:02.520
The teeth closed on the front of the car.

23:03.400 --> 23:05.880
The three kids looked down the red throat.

23:06.840 --> 23:08.840
There were teeth all the way down.

23:10.120 --> 23:10.520
Quick!

23:11.160 --> 23:11.560
Move!

23:12.120 --> 23:13.000
Shouted DJ.

23:14.120 --> 23:16.200
The back window of the car was open.

23:16.920 --> 23:17.800
They went through it.

23:19.080 --> 23:23.160
Then the door of the house closed and the car went down the throat.

23:24.600 --> 23:25.800
Everything went quiet.

23:27.160 --> 23:29.800
The carpet sat quietly on the stairs.

23:30.760 --> 23:33.880
The walls and the floors were in the right places.

23:34.760 --> 23:39.080
It doesn't know we're here, said DJ quietly.

23:40.040 --> 23:44.440
Now, we must find the fire and put water on it.

23:45.640 --> 23:49.560
I don't think that's a good idea, said chowder.

23:50.280 --> 23:51.400
Do you want to die?

23:51.960 --> 23:52.760
Ask DJ.

23:53.480 --> 23:54.760
Okay, okay.

23:55.640 --> 23:56.920
Let's look for the heart.

23:57.720 --> 23:58.440
Chowder said.

23:59.720 --> 24:01.880
Be careful, said DJ.

24:02.760 --> 24:03.960
And stay to go!

24:04.600 --> 24:07.240
Suddenly, DJ fell through the floor.

24:08.360 --> 24:14.280
There was a loud breaking sound and Jenny and Chowder fell through after him into the dark.

24:15.800 --> 24:17.080
They were in a big room.

24:17.960 --> 24:20.200
There were a lot of children's things there.

24:21.640 --> 24:23.640
Look at this, said DJ.

24:24.600 --> 24:26.680
It was an old circus caravan.

24:27.720 --> 24:29.880
The colours were now old and dark.

24:30.600 --> 24:32.200
It was in two parts.

24:33.160 --> 24:36.040
On one part of the caravan was some words.

24:37.000 --> 24:39.240
Constance, the giantess.

24:40.520 --> 24:42.520
The kids looked at it quietly.

24:44.040 --> 24:47.480
This was beautiful a long time ago, said DJ.

24:48.280 --> 24:49.160
Let's look in it.

24:50.360 --> 24:52.520
Let's not, said chowder.

24:53.800 --> 24:54.920
DJ went in.

24:55.880 --> 24:57.480
There were pictures on the walls.

24:58.280 --> 25:01.240
Then he saw something in the cement floor.

25:02.280 --> 25:04.280
It looked like a big body.

25:05.800 --> 25:07.400
Suddenly the floor moved.

25:08.200 --> 25:11.080
The floor's breaking, shouted DJ.

25:12.040 --> 25:14.120
Then there was a strong wind.

25:15.000 --> 25:17.480
It's Constance, cried Jenny.

25:18.120 --> 25:19.000
She's angry.

25:19.640 --> 25:21.560
She doesn't like people near her.

25:23.160 --> 25:25.960
Everything in the room started to move and break.

25:26.760 --> 25:28.200
The sounds were terrible.

25:29.240 --> 25:30.920
Constance knew they were there.

25:32.840 --> 25:35.400
The wind threw the three kids out of the room.

25:36.200 --> 25:38.040
Ron, shouted DJ.

25:39.320 --> 25:41.240
Chowder was at the top of the stairs.

25:41.800 --> 25:42.920
The throat opened.

25:43.960 --> 25:46.760
Suddenly the stairs went down the throat.

25:47.640 --> 25:49.560
The throat pulled at chowder too.

25:50.680 --> 25:52.760
The house gave a terrible cry,

25:53.400 --> 25:54.760
but chowder didn't fall.

25:55.960 --> 25:57.400
He held one of the teeth.

25:58.520 --> 26:00.360
DJ tried to pull him up.

26:01.320 --> 26:04.040
Then the carpet tongue came out quickly

26:04.040 --> 26:06.040
and threw DJ down the throat.

26:06.840 --> 26:08.680
No, cried Jenny.

26:09.800 --> 26:11.880
The house moved up and down.

26:13.000 --> 26:16.200
Then she saw something red at the back of the throat.

26:16.920 --> 26:18.360
She pulled on it hard.

26:19.160 --> 26:21.320
The house moved up and down again.

26:22.040 --> 26:23.080
I can't hold.

26:24.040 --> 26:27.000
She shouted and fell down the red throat.

26:27.960 --> 26:29.480
But there was someone close.

26:30.280 --> 26:31.160
It was DJ.

26:32.440 --> 26:34.120
Journey held onto his legs.

26:34.920 --> 26:36.920
DJ held onto Chowder's legs.

26:38.200 --> 26:42.360
Then a strong wind and a lot of water came up the throat.

26:43.240 --> 26:46.040
It threw the three kids out of the open door.

26:47.400 --> 26:51.720
DJ ran into the street as a car stopped in front of the house.

26:53.880 --> 26:55.880
DJ held onto Chowder's legs.

27:01.320 --> 27:02.120
Chapter 6

27:03.400 --> 27:05.160
Mr. Nebakracker's Story

27:06.840 --> 27:08.440
It was Mr. Nebakracker.

27:09.080 --> 27:10.200
He was very white.

27:11.320 --> 27:13.240
No, cried Chowder.

27:13.800 --> 27:14.520
You're dead.

27:15.160 --> 27:15.800
Go away.

27:17.000 --> 27:17.960
You go away.

27:18.760 --> 27:20.600
Said Mr. Nebakracker angrily.

27:21.240 --> 27:22.360
He's not dead.

27:23.000 --> 27:24.200
Said DJ happily.

27:24.920 --> 27:27.080
Of course I'm not dead.

27:27.960 --> 27:29.480
Is it Halloween today?

27:30.360 --> 27:32.680
Go away or you're going to die.

27:33.960 --> 27:36.040
Mr. Nebakracker turned to the house.

27:37.240 --> 27:38.840
I'm home, my love.

27:40.200 --> 27:41.800
The house started to cry.

27:43.160 --> 27:45.720
Look at your windows and your walls.

27:46.440 --> 27:47.560
He said quietly.

27:48.520 --> 27:49.960
But it isn't a problem.

27:50.680 --> 27:52.040
We can make it better.

27:53.320 --> 27:56.200
We're going to have a nice quiet evening.

27:56.920 --> 27:57.960
Like every year.

27:58.760 --> 27:59.640
No children.

28:00.680 --> 28:01.400
Only us.

28:03.080 --> 28:05.000
It's her, said DJ.

28:05.720 --> 28:07.080
The house is her.

28:08.040 --> 28:09.240
Mr. Nebakracker,

28:10.040 --> 28:11.640
I know about Constance.

28:12.520 --> 28:13.320
I saw her.

28:14.760 --> 28:17.080
There was a surprised sound from the house.

28:18.280 --> 28:19.720
Were you in my house?

28:20.520 --> 28:22.040
Cried Mr. Nebakracker.

28:23.000 --> 28:25.400
I know she died, said DJ.

28:27.000 --> 28:30.360
I loved her, said Mr. Nebakracker sadly.

28:31.720 --> 28:33.720
He told them Constance's story.

28:34.840 --> 28:37.000
The kids saw the pictures in their heads.

28:38.440 --> 28:41.400
They were in Constance's caravan at the circus.

28:42.360 --> 28:44.920
There was happy music and circus sounds.

28:45.960 --> 28:49.320
People looked at Constance the giantess in her caravan.

28:50.360 --> 28:52.440
They laughed and threw things at her.

28:53.640 --> 28:55.240
She was sad and alone.

28:56.600 --> 28:59.800
She looked at the floor and tried to forget the people.

29:01.080 --> 29:04.200
One day a boy threw old vegetables at her.

29:05.480 --> 29:08.920
Constance was very angry and she shouted at the boy.

29:10.280 --> 29:12.680
A young man came and held the boy's arm.

29:13.560 --> 29:15.000
It was Mr. Nebakracker.

29:16.200 --> 29:19.320
That night he went to Constance's caravan

29:19.400 --> 29:20.200
and they talked.

29:21.320 --> 29:23.080
He thought she was beautiful.

29:24.520 --> 29:28.520
Mr. Nebakracker took Constance's caravan away from the circus.

29:29.400 --> 29:31.320
They found a place to build a home.

29:33.320 --> 29:36.840
Mr. Nebakracker started to build a lovely house

29:37.480 --> 29:39.480
and made a big hole for the cement.

29:40.760 --> 29:42.840
The cement was almost ready.

29:43.720 --> 29:46.520
He decided to break Constance's caravan.

29:47.480 --> 29:50.200
Then something terrible happened.

29:51.240 --> 29:52.760
He heard a loud cry.

29:53.640 --> 29:57.960
It was Halloween and some young children came to Trick or Treat.

29:58.840 --> 30:02.440
When they saw Constance, they started to throw things at her.

30:03.240 --> 30:06.040
Go away, shouted Mr. Nebakracker.

30:07.240 --> 30:09.240
Some of the things hit Constance.

30:10.040 --> 30:11.720
The children just laughed.

30:13.000 --> 30:15.240
It's always going to be like this.

30:15.880 --> 30:16.840
Cried Constance.

30:17.720 --> 30:19.160
She shouted at the children.

30:19.720 --> 30:26.040
She tried to run but she fell into the big hole and the cement fell on top of her.

30:27.240 --> 30:33.160
There was a terrible cry and Constance, the giantess, died.

30:35.880 --> 30:38.440
So I've finished the house.

30:39.240 --> 30:41.080
Mr. Nebakracker said to DJ.

30:41.880 --> 30:45.080
She died but she didn't leave.

30:46.440 --> 30:50.760
She hates children and she's often angry at them.

30:51.800 --> 30:53.720
I try to stop her.

30:54.440 --> 30:57.640
At Halloween, it's very hard.

30:59.320 --> 31:01.960
The house started to make loud sounds.

31:02.760 --> 31:04.360
I'm coming, my love.

31:05.080 --> 31:06.440
Said Mr. Nebakracker.

31:07.240 --> 31:08.920
And you children must go.

31:09.720 --> 31:11.720
But DJ held his arm.

31:12.760 --> 31:16.280
No, Mr. Nebakracker, you have your life.

31:17.320 --> 31:19.400
It's time to leave Constance.

31:20.920 --> 31:22.600
She's all I have.

31:23.720 --> 31:25.480
Said Mr. Nebakracker, sadly.

31:26.600 --> 31:28.200
No, said DJ.

31:28.920 --> 31:30.280
You have me too.

31:31.240 --> 31:32.200
I'm your friend.

31:33.640 --> 31:37.000
He took Mr. Nebakracker's hand and they walked away.

31:39.160 --> 31:42.760
Mr. Nebakracker was happy, but the house wasn't.

31:43.560 --> 31:45.560
It was very, very angry.

31:46.760 --> 31:49.160
Suddenly, there was a terrible sound.

31:50.440 --> 31:52.600
DJ and Mr. Nebakracker looked back.

31:53.560 --> 32:02.840
The house was moving again.

32:03.480 --> 32:05.800
Chapter 7

32:06.840 --> 32:08.360
Goodbye, Constance.

32:10.440 --> 32:14.520
Mr. Nebakracker and the three kids ran to the danger zone.

32:15.480 --> 32:16.840
The house was behind them.

32:17.480 --> 32:18.360
It was angry.

32:19.000 --> 32:19.880
It was strong.

32:20.680 --> 32:21.960
And it was close.

32:23.880 --> 32:27.560
Mr. Nebakracker threw hard bits of cement at the house.

32:28.280 --> 32:30.840
Stay away from them, he shouted.

32:31.640 --> 32:34.760
Constance saw Mr. Nebakracker and stopped.

32:35.640 --> 32:36.520
She was quiet.

32:37.480 --> 32:40.920
You were a bad girl, said Mr. Nebakracker.

32:41.640 --> 32:43.000
I must do this.

32:44.520 --> 32:47.400
He carefully took some dynamite from his bag.

32:48.520 --> 32:51.480
Constance saw it and gave an angry cry.

32:52.840 --> 32:55.800
Suddenly, there were lights and a loud sound.

32:56.600 --> 33:00.120
It was the big digger and chowder was the driver.

33:01.400 --> 33:03.160
How did you learn to drive this?

33:03.800 --> 33:05.080
Jenny asked chowder.

33:05.800 --> 33:06.520
I didn't.

33:07.320 --> 33:08.280
answered chowder.

33:09.240 --> 33:11.320
DJ ran to Mr. Nebakracker.

33:12.040 --> 33:13.800
He gave DJ the dynamite.

33:14.520 --> 33:15.880
Take this, he said.

33:16.680 --> 33:18.040
I started it.

33:18.040 --> 33:18.920
You finish it.

33:19.640 --> 33:20.920
The dynamite's ready.

33:21.560 --> 33:24.680
You have three minutes and 18 seconds.

33:26.040 --> 33:27.480
DJ looked at the house.

33:28.760 --> 33:30.120
Where do I throw it?

33:30.600 --> 33:31.160
He thought.

33:32.600 --> 33:37.960
Then he saw the smoke and remembered the fire, the heart.

33:39.640 --> 33:42.360
The digger and the house were now face to face.

33:43.560 --> 33:48.040
Then DJ saw the tall crane high over the danger zone.

33:49.160 --> 33:50.840
Chowder, he shouted.

33:51.560 --> 33:54.840
Try to move the house under the crane.

33:56.440 --> 33:59.880
Suddenly, the digger turned and moved to the crane.

34:00.920 --> 34:03.560
The house tried to turn, but it fell.

34:04.520 --> 34:05.960
There was a loud sound.

34:07.000 --> 34:08.760
The house started to break.

34:10.200 --> 34:13.800
There were parts of the house all over the danger zone.

34:15.240 --> 34:17.720
DJ and Jenny went up in the crane.

34:18.760 --> 34:19.960
But where was Chowder?

34:21.320 --> 34:22.360
Then they heard him.

34:23.480 --> 34:25.800
Hey, shouted chowder.

34:25.800 --> 34:26.760
I did it.

34:27.320 --> 34:29.880
Me, the house is dead.

34:31.160 --> 34:32.120
But it wasn't dead.

34:33.080 --> 34:38.120
All the parts of the house came back together again to make a new house.

34:39.240 --> 34:42.360
This time it was a worse monster than before.

34:43.080 --> 34:44.520
It looked terrible.

34:46.440 --> 34:49.160
Chowder drove the digger quickly to the crane.

34:50.120 --> 34:51.960
The new monster house followed.

34:52.920 --> 34:57.000
The door opened and the mouth closed on the arm of the digger.

34:57.800 --> 34:59.480
It took the digger up high.

35:00.280 --> 35:03.720
Chowder fell out and then the tongue took the digger.

35:04.520 --> 35:05.400
Chowder ran.

35:06.200 --> 35:07.240
The house followed.

35:09.080 --> 35:11.240
DJ looked down the arm of the crane.

35:11.800 --> 35:12.680
He was frightened.

35:13.400 --> 35:14.760
I can't do it.

35:14.760 --> 35:17.640
He said, you can, said Jenny.

35:18.120 --> 35:19.240
And she smiled at him.

35:20.200 --> 35:22.840
Yes, he thought, or can.

35:24.440 --> 35:26.120
He moved to the end of the arm.

35:27.720 --> 35:28.760
DJ looked down.

35:29.800 --> 35:30.760
There was the house.

35:31.800 --> 35:32.840
There was the smoke.

35:34.360 --> 35:36.680
DJ threw the dynamite into the smoke,

35:37.560 --> 35:39.080
into the heart of the house.

35:41.160 --> 35:42.840
Everything was very quiet.

35:43.880 --> 35:45.160
The house didn't move.

35:46.360 --> 35:48.440
It didn't look like a monster house now.

35:49.320 --> 35:51.800
It looked clean and quiet like before.

35:53.320 --> 35:54.280
The kids waited.

35:55.720 --> 35:56.520
Was it over?

35:57.400 --> 36:00.200
Did DJ throw the dynamite in the right place?

36:02.280 --> 36:05.240
Little sounds started to come from the house.

36:06.360 --> 36:08.280
Then they were bigger and louder.

36:09.560 --> 36:15.560
Suddenly there was a great white light and the house was a ball of fire.

36:16.440 --> 36:22.040
Cement, windows, walls and floor rained down from the sky.

36:23.400 --> 36:25.480
The kids shouted and danced.

36:26.120 --> 36:27.080
We did it!

36:27.640 --> 36:29.080
The house is dead!

36:30.600 --> 36:32.120
Then something happened.

36:33.240 --> 36:37.000
A strong wind came and moved all the parts of the house.

36:37.880 --> 36:39.960
They all came together in the sky.

36:41.080 --> 36:44.760
It was constant, big and beautiful again.

36:46.200 --> 36:49.240
Constance said DJ quietly.

36:50.840 --> 36:52.440
Mr. Nevercracker looked up.

36:53.560 --> 36:54.280
My love!

36:55.240 --> 36:55.880
Goodbye!

36:56.680 --> 36:57.320
He cried.

36:58.840 --> 37:00.120
Constance smiled.

37:01.160 --> 37:03.800
She put her arms around Mr. Nevercracker.

37:05.000 --> 37:06.520
Then the wind came again.

37:07.400 --> 37:08.840
And there was only the sky.

37:10.600 --> 37:13.000
I'm sorry about your house.

37:13.640 --> 37:17.000
Um, wife, said DJ.

37:17.960 --> 37:21.880
Constance is happy now, said Mr. Nevercracker.

37:23.080 --> 37:24.600
There was a light in his eyes.

37:25.640 --> 37:27.880
And I can live my life.

37:29.160 --> 37:29.640
Thank you.

37:31.960 --> 37:33.400
It was Halloween night.

37:34.360 --> 37:37.480
There were trick-or-treaters on Mr. Nevercracker's lawn.

37:38.200 --> 37:39.880
They came to get their things.

37:40.680 --> 37:45.560
There were bikes, basketballs, footballs and kites.

37:47.000 --> 37:49.560
DJ gave the bike back to the little girl.

37:50.520 --> 37:51.080
Thank you.

37:51.720 --> 37:53.400
She said and smiled.

37:54.520 --> 37:58.600
Then she went between the trees and the lovely gardens of Oak Street.

38:00.120 --> 38:02.360
Jenny put her arms around the boys.

38:03.320 --> 38:07.160
We must do something together again soon, she said.

38:08.120 --> 38:09.640
Then she left with her mom.

38:11.320 --> 38:14.840
We are too old for trick-or-treating, said Chowder.

38:15.480 --> 38:17.000
Yes, said DJ.

38:17.960 --> 38:20.440
But we heard a very difficult evening.

38:21.320 --> 38:23.080
Yes, said DJ.

38:24.200 --> 38:25.480
Time for treats?

38:26.440 --> 38:28.440
Yeah, time for treats.

38:29.560 --> 38:31.560
And the boys ran down the road.

38:31.560 --> 38:37.720
Some people came out of the big hole in Mr. Nevercracker's garden.

38:38.760 --> 38:40.120
Bones was first.

38:41.080 --> 38:42.760
He looked very surprised.

38:43.880 --> 38:46.200
Then the two policemen came out.

38:47.400 --> 38:48.520
Bones looked at them.

38:49.480 --> 38:52.520
Happy Halloween, he said and smiled.

38:53.640 --> 38:55.800
He held his red kite in his hands.

38:56.760 --> 38:58.760
You too, said Londers.

38:59.400 --> 39:00.760
Happy Halloween.

